{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848203313,"sessionID":"ses_287331ec5ffe8Mnu800CZapmVx","part":{"id":"prt_d78cd1c41001LJAO3uTk81cWiK","messageID":"msg_d78cd0bf6001uDIRmJ2Gmu0h7Z","sessionID":"ses_287331ec5ffe8Mnu800CZapmVx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_264d10ad7bf04c7b87ebad9c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement an HTTP reverse proxy core in `pkg/router` to route external HTTP requests to dynamically created sandbox endpoints managed by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs. This enables external clients to access agent sessions and code interpreter environments through a unified entry point.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AR-007 controller creates sandbox Pods based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs. Currently:\n12: \n13: - **No external access mechanism**: Sandboxes are isolated within the cluster with no way for external clients to reach them\n14: - **Manual port forwarding**: Operators must manually set up port forwarding or Ingress for each sandbox\n15: - **Inconsistent routing**: Each sandbox type requires different access patterns\n16: - **No unified entry point**: Clients need to manage multiple endpoint addresses\n17: \n18: ### Goal\n19: \n20: Provide a reverse proxy that:\n21: - Dynamically discovers active sandbox endpoints from AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter status\n22: - Routes HTTP requests to the appropriate sandbox based on routing rules\n23: - Supports path-based and header-based routing\n24: - Manages connection lifecycle and health checking\n25: - Provides authentication and rate limiting at the proxy level\n26: \n27: ### Value\n28: - Simplifies client access to sandbox environments\n29: - Centralized authentication and security at the proxy layer\n30: - Dynamic scaling without manual reconfiguration\n31: - Consistent routing across different sandbox types\n32: - Enables multi-tenant access control\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Scope\n37: \n38: ### In-Scope\n39: \n40: | Deliverable | Description |\n41: |-------------|-------------|\n42: | Reverse Proxy Server | Core HTTP server with dynamic backend management |\n43: | Endpoint Discovery | Watch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRs for active endpoints |\n44: | Routing Engine | Path-based, header-based, and weighted routing |\n45: | Health Checker | Periodic health checks for backend endpoints |\n46: | Connection Pool | Reusable connections to backends with keep-alive |\n47: | Access Control | Authentication middleware and rate limiting |\n48: | Metrics | Request latency, error rates, backend health |\n49: | Unit Tests | Core routing logic coverage >60% |\n50: \n51: ### Code Structure\n52: \n53: ```\n54: pkg/router/\n55: ├── server.go                     # HTTP server with proxy logic\n56: ├── router.go                     # Router interface and implementation\n57: ├── discovery/\n58: │   ├── discovery.go              # Endpoint discovery from CRs\n59: │   ├── agentruntime_watcher.go   # AgentRuntime endpoint watcher\n60: │   └── codeinterpreter_watcher.go # CodeInterpreter endpoint watcher\n61: ├── backend/\n62: │   ├── backend.go                # Backend pool management\n63: │   ├── healthcheck.go            # Health checking logic\n64: │   └── connpool.go               # Connection pooling\n65: ├── routing/\n66: │   ├── router.go                 # Routing rule engine\n67: │   ├── path_routing.go           # Path-based routing\n68: │   └── header_routing.go         # Header-based routing\n69: ├── middleware/\n70: │   ├── auth.go                   # Authentication middleware\n71: │   ├── ratelimit.go              # Rate limiting\n72: │   └── logging.go                # Request logging\n73: ├── metrics/\n74: │   └── metrics.go                # Prometheus metrics\n75: ├── config/\n76: │   └── config.go                 # Configuration struct\n77: └── router_test.go                # Unit tests\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Configuration\n81: \n82: The router supports these configuration options:\n83: \n84: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n85: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n86: | listenAddress | string | \":8080\" | Proxy listen address |\n87: | backendTimeout | duration | 30s | Timeout for backend requests |\n88: | idleTimeout | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n89: | maxConnsPerBackend | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n90: | healthCheckInterval | duration | 10s | Backend health check interval |\n91: | healthCheckTimeout | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n92: | rateLimitEnabled | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n93: | rateLimitRPS | int | 100 | Requests per second per client |\n94: | authEnabled | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n95: | watchNamespaces | []string | all | Namespaces to watch for CRs |\n96: \n97: ### Out-of-Scope\n98: - TCP/UDP proxying (HTTP only)\n99: - TLS termination (handled by Ingress)\n100: - WebSocket support (future enhancement)\n101: - Multi-cluster routing (separate module)\n102: - Custom routing rules CRD (future enhancement)\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Impact Analysis\n107: \n108: ### Dependencies\n109: \n110: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n111: |------------|--------|---------|\n112: | github.com/volcano/sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client for CR watch |\n113: | github.com/volcano/sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter types |\n114: | k8s.io/client-go/informers | ^0.34 | Cached list/watch for CRs |\n115: | k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache | ^0.34 | SharedIndexInformer for CR watching |\n116: | github.com/gin-gonic/gin | ^1.9 | HTTP server (optional, can use stdlib) |\n117: | github.com/prometheus/client_golang | ^1.20 | Prometheus metrics |\n118: \n119: ### Upstream Dependencies\n120: \n121: - **AR-007 K8s Reconciler** — Creates sandboxes that the router proxies to\n122: - **AR-005/AR-006 Sandbox Creation** — Endpoints are discovered from these APIs\n123: \n124: ### Downstream Consumers\n125: \n126: 1. **External Clients** — Access agent runtimes and code interpreters through the proxy\n127: 2. **Ingress Controllers** — Can route to the proxy as a backend\n128: 3. **Monitoring** — Proxy metrics for operational visibility\n129: 4. **API Gateway** — Can use the proxy as a transport layer\n130: \n131: ### Risks\n132: \n133: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n134: |------|----------|------------|\n135: | Backend not ready | Medium | Health checks, retry with backoff |\n136: | Proxy becomes bottleneck | Medium | Connection pooling, horizontal scaling |\n137: | Stale endpoints | Medium | Watch-based discovery with immediate updates |\n138: | Authentication bypass | High | Middleware validation, default deny |\n139: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | Connection limits, rate limiting |\n140: | Routing loops | Low | Backend self-referential checks |\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## Alternatives Considered\n145: \n146: ### Option 1: Custom Reverse Proxy with CR Watch (Selected)\n147: \n148: **Approach**: Implement a custom HTTP reverse proxy that watches AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRs and dynamically updates backend pool.\n149: \n150: **Pros**:\n151: - Full control over routing logic\n152: - Tight integration with CR status for endpoint discovery\n153: - Can implement custom health checking\n154: - Lightweight compared to generic proxies\n155: \n156: **Cons**:\n157: - Additional code to maintain\n158: - Need to implement connection pooling\n159: \n160: **Decision**: Selected — provides the best integration with the existing CR-based workflow and allows custom routing logic.\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### Option 2: Use NGINX Ingress Controller\n165: \n166: **Approach**: Configure NGINX Ingress with Dynamic Configuration or Kubernetes Gateway API.\n167: \n168: **Pros**:\n169: - Mature, production-tested reverse proxy\n170: - Rich routing features\n171: - Built-in load balancing\n172: \n173: **Cons**:\n174: - Requires additional CRDs for dynamic backend updates\n175: - Less visibility into CR status\n176: - Heavyweight for simple proxy use case\n177: \n178: **Decision**: Rejected — adds complexity and external dependency when a simpler solution suffices.\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Option 3: Use Envoy Proxy with Control Plane\n183: \n184: **Approach**: Deploy Envoy with a custom control plane that programs routes based on CRs.\n185: \n186: **Pros**:\n187: - High-performance proxy\n188: - Rich feature set\n189: - Production-tested at scale\n190: \n191: **Cons**:\n192: - Significant complexity in control plane implementation\n193: - Requires maintaining Envoy configurations\n194: - Over-engineered for the current scope\n195: \n196: **Decision**: Rejected — the complexity outweighs the benefits for the current use case.\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Option 4: Use Kubernetes Service with NodePort\n201: \n202: **Approach**: Expose each sandbox as a NodePort Service.\n203: \n204: **Pros**:\n205: - Native Kubernetes approach\n206: - No custom proxy code\n207: \n208: **Cons**:\n209: - Port exhaustion with many sandboxes\n210: - No path-based routing\n211: - No unified access point\n212: - Security concerns with node ports\n213: \n214: **Decision**: Rejected — does not provide the required routing capabilities.\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## Implementation Plan\n219: \n220: ### Phase 1: Router Foundation\n221: - [ ] Create pkg/router module structure\n222: - [ ] Implement Config with defaults and CLI flags\n223: - [ ] Create Router interface and basic implementation\n224: - [ ] Set up HTTP server with graceful shutdown\n225: \n226: ### Phase 2: Endpoint Discovery\n227: - [ ] Implement CR watcher for AgentRuntime\n228: - [ ] Implement CR watcher for CodeInterpreter\n229: - [ ] Extract endpoint info from CR status\n230: - [ ] Handle CR add/update/delete events\n231: \n232: ### Phase 3: Backend Management\n233: - [ ] Implement backend pool with dynamic updates\n234: - [ ] Implement connection pooling\n235: - [ ] Implement health checking with configurable intervals\n236: - [ ] Handle backend failures and recovery\n237: \n238: ### Phase 4: Routing Engine\n239: - [ ] Implement path-based routing\n240: - [ ] Implement header-based routing\n241: - [ ] Implement default routing strategy\n242: - [ ] Add routing rule configuration\n243: \n244: ### Phase 5: Middleware\n245: - [ ] Add request logging middleware\n246: - [ ] Implement rate limiting (token bucket)\n247: - [ ] Add authentication middleware\n248: - [ ] Add metrics collection\n249: \n250: ### Phase 6: Testing\n251: - [ ] Unit tests for routing logic\n252: - [ ] Unit tests for backend pool\n253: - [ ] Mock tests for health checking\n254: - [ ] Integration tests with mock API server\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Acceptance Criteria\n259: \n260: - [ ] Router starts and listens on configured address\n261: - [ ] Endpoints are discovered from AgentRuntime CRs\n262: - [ ] Endpoints are discovered from CodeInterpreter CRs\n263: - [ ] Requests are routed to the correct backend based on path\n264: - [ ] Requests are routed based on headers when configured\n265: - [ ] Unhealthy backends are removed from the pool\n266: - [ ] Connection pooling works correctly\n267: - [ ] Rate limiting restricts requests when enabled\n268: - [ ] Authentication middleware validates requests\n269: - [ ] Metrics are exported for Prometheus\n270: - [ ] Graceful shutdown terminates existing connections\n271: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >60% coverage\n272: - [ ] Router integrates with AR-007 controller for lifecycle\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an HTTP reverse proxy core in `pkg/router` to route external HTTP requests to dynamically created sandbox endpoints managed by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs. This enables external clients to access agent sessions and code interpreter environments through a unified entry point.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AR-007 controller creates sandbox Pods based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs. Currently:\n\n- **No external access mechanism**: Sandboxes are isolated within the cluster with no way for external clients to reach them\n- **Manual port forwarding**: Operators must manually set up port forwarding or Ingress for each sandbox\n- **Inconsistent routing**: Each sandbox type requires different access patterns\n- **No unified entry point**: Clients need to manage multiple endpoint addresses\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide a reverse proxy that:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775848203292,"end":1775848203311}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848203317,"sessionID":"ses_287331ec5ffe8Mnu800CZapmVx","part":{"id":"prt_d78cd201d001VkBaPaEVZsj2n0","messageID":"msg_d78cd0bf6001uDIRmJ2Gmu0h7Z","sessionID":"ses_287331ec5ffe8Mnu800CZapmVx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c3984c823bfb4c038e53731c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/server.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/server.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"net/http\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"os/signal\"\n9: \t\"syscall\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: )\n12: \n13: type Router struct {\n14: \tconfig        *Config\n15: \tserver        *http.Server\n16: \tpool          *BackendPool\n17: \tproxy         *Proxy\n18: \trouteHandler  *RouteHandler\n19: \thealthChecker *HealthChecker\n20: \trateLimiter   *RateLimiter\n21: \tauthenticator *Authenticator\n22: \tlogger        *Logger\n23: \tmetrics       *Metrics\n24: }\n25: \n26: func NewRouter(config *Config) *Router {\n27: \tif config == nil {\n28: \t\tconfig = DefaultConfig()\n29: \t}\n30: \n31: \tpool := NewBackendPool()\n32: \tproxy := NewProxy(config.BackendTimeout, config.IdleTimeout, config.MaxConnsPerBackend)\n33: \trouteHandler := NewRouteHandler(pool, []string{\"X-Backend\", \"Content-Type\"})\n34: \thealthChecker := NewHealthChecker(pool, config.HealthCheckInterval, config.HealthCheckTimeout, 3)\n35: \trateLimiter := NewRateLimiter(config.RateLimitRPS, config.RateLimitRPS*2, config.RateLimitEnabled)\n36: \tauthenticator := NewAuthenticator(config.AuthToken, config.AuthEnabled)\n37: \tlogger := NewLogger(nil)\n38: \tmetrics := NewMetrics()\n39: \n40: \trouter := &Router{\n41: \t\tconfig:        config,\n42: \t\tpool:          pool,\n43: \t\tproxy:         proxy,\n44: \t\trouteHandler:  routeHandler,\n45: \t\thealthChecker: healthChecker,\n46: \t\trateLimiter:   rateLimiter,\n47: \t\tauthenticator: authenticator,\n48: \t\tlogger:        logger,\n49: \t\tmetrics:       metrics,\n50: \t}\n51: \n52: \tmux := http.NewServeMux()\n53: \tmux.HandleFunc(\"/\", router.handleRequest)\n54: \n55: \thandler := logger.Middleware(mux)\n56: \thandler = rateLimiter.Middleware(handler)\n57: \thandler = authenticator.Middleware(handler)\n58: \n59: \trouter.server = &http.Server{\n60: \t\tAddr:         config.ListenAddress,\n61: \t\tHandler:      handler,\n62: \t\tReadTimeout:  config.BackendTimeout,\n63: \t\tWriteTimeout: config.BackendTimeout,\n64: \t\tIdleTimeout:  config.IdleTimeout,\n65: \t}\n66: \n67: \treturn router\n68: }\n69: \n70: func (r *Router) Start() error {\n71: \tgo func() {\n72: \t\tfmt.Printf(\"Starting router on %s\\n\", r.config.ListenAddress)\n73: \t\tif err := r.server.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n74: \t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Server error: %v\\n\", err)\n75: \t\t}\n76: \t}()\n77: \n78: \tr.healthChecker.Start()\n79: \n80: \treturn nil\n81: }\n82: \n83: func (r *Router) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n84: \tr.healthChecker.Stop()\n85: \n86: \tfmt.Println(\"Shutting down router...\")\n87: \treturn r.server.Shutdown(ctx)\n88: }\n89: \n90: func (r *Router) handleRequest(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request) {\n91: \tstart := time.Now()\n92: \n93: \tbackend := r.routeHandler.GetBackendForRequest(req)\n94: \tif backend == nil {\n95: \t\tr.metrics.IncErrors(\"not_found\")\n96: \t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n97: \t\treturn\n98: \t}\n99: \n100: \tr.proxy.ServeHTTP(w, req, backend)\n101: \n102: \tduration := time.Since(start).Seconds()\n103: \tr.metrics.RecordRequestDuration(req.Method, req.URL.Path, backend.Name, duration)\n104: \tr.metrics.IncBackendRequests(backend.Name, \"success\")\n105: }\n106: \n107: func (r *Router) GetPool() *BackendPool {\n108: \treturn r.pool\n109: }\n110: \n111: func (r *Router) GetConfig() *Config {\n112: \treturn r.config\n113: }\n114: \n115: func (r *Router) GetHealthChecker() *HealthChecker {\n116: \treturn r.healthChecker\n117: }\n118: \n119: func (r *Router) GetMetrics() *Metrics {\n120: \treturn r.metrics\n121: }\n122: \n123: func (r *Router) AddBackend(key, endpoint, pathPrefix, name string) error {\n124: \treturn r.pool.AddBackend(key, endpoint, pathPrefix, name)\n125: }\n126: \n127: func (r *Router) RemoveBackend(key string) {\n128: \tr.pool.RemoveBackend(key)\n129: }\n130: \n131: func (r *Router) SetHeaderRoute(headerName, headerValue, backendKey string) {\n132: \tr.pool.SetHeaderRoute(headerName, headerValue, backendKey)\n133: }\n134: \n135: func RunWithSignal(cfg *Config) error {\n136: \trouter := NewRouter(cfg)\n137: \n138: \tif err := router.Start(); err != nil {\n139: \t\treturn err\n140: \t}\n141: \n142: \tsigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n143: \tsignal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n144: \n145: \t<-sigCh\n146: \tfmt.Println(\"\\nReceived shutdown signal\")\n147: \n148: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n149: \tdefer cancel()\n150: \n151: \treturn router.Shutdown(ctx)\n152: }\n\n(End of file - total 152 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/signal\"\n\t\"syscall\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\ntype Router struct {\n\tconfig        *Config\n\tserver        *http.Server\n\tpool          *BackendPool\n\tproxy         *Proxy\n\trouteHandler  *RouteHandler\n\thealthChecker *HealthChecker\n\trateLimiter   *RateLimiter","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/server.go","time":{"start":1775848203296,"end":1775848203315}}}}
